McDOWELL v. FRATERNAL UNION OF AMERICA. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. October 7, 1902.) No. 1,124. In Error to the Circuit Court of the United States for the Northern District of Georgia. Grigsby E. Thomas, Jr., and B. H. Hill, for plaintiff in error. Shepard Bryan, for defendant in error.

Before PARDEE, McCORMICK, and SHELBY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The judgment of the circuit court is affirmed. See Bigelow v. Insurance Co., 93 U. S. 284, 23 L. Ed. 918.
